{"title_page": "Jackson Avery", "text_new": "{{Lead too short|date=May 2012}}\n{{Infobox character\n| name = Jackson Avery\n| series = [[Grey's Anatomy]]\n| image = [[File:Jesse-williams-greys.jpg|220px]]\n| caption = The [[Grey's Anatomy (season 9)|Season 9]] Promotional Photo of [[Jesse Williams (actor)|Jesse Williams]] as '''Dr. Jackson Avery'''\n| portrayer = [[Jesse Williams (actor)|Jesse Williams]]\n| first = \"[[Invasion (Grey's Anatomy)|Invasion]]\" (6.05) <br> October 15, 2009 <br> (as recurring cast) <br> \"[[Grey's Anatomy (season 7)#ep127|With You I'm Born Again]]\" (7.01) <br> September 23, 2010 <br> (as series regular)\n| creator = [[Shonda Rhimes]]\n| occupation = [[Attending physician|Attending]] [[Plastic surgery|plastic surgeon]] and [[Otolaryngology|ENT]]<br>Board [[Chairman]] of Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital\n| title = Chief of Plastic Surgery<br>[[Doctor of Medicine|M.D]]<br>[[Fellow of the American College of Surgeons|F.A.C.S.]]\n| spouse = {{marriage|[[April Kepner]]|2013|2016|reason=divorced}}\n| children = Samuel Norbert Avery (son via April, deceased) <br>Harriet Kepner-Avery (daughter via April) \n| significant_other = [[Lexie Grey]] <br> [[Stephanie Edwards (Grey's Anatomy)|Stephanie Edwards]] <br> [[Maggie Pierce]] <br> Victoria \"Vic\" Hughes <br> \u2018Priya\u2019\n| family = Robert Avery (father)<br>Catherine Avery (mother)<br>Harper Avery (paternal grandfather, deceased)<br> [[Richard Webber]] (step-father)\n}}\n'''Jackson Avery''', [[Doctor of Medicine|M.D.]] is a fictional character in the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] [[prime time]] [[medical drama]], ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'', portrayed by actor [[Jesse Williams (actor)|Jesse Williams]].<ref name=\"ABC.com\">{{cite web|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/greys-anatomy/bios/jackson-avery|title=Jesse Williams as Jackson Avery|work=[[Grey's Anatomy]]|publisher=[[American Broadcasting Company]]|accessdate=December 7, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104031102/http://abc.go.com/shows/greys-anatomy/bios/jackson-avery|archivedate=November 4, 2013}}</ref> The character was created by series creator and executive producer, [[Shonda Rhimes]]. He was introduced in [[Grey's Anatomy (season 6)|season six]] episode \"[[Invasion (Grey's Anatomy)|Invasion]]\" as a surgical resident formerly from Mercy West Medical Center when it merges with Seattle Grace Hospital.\n\nWilliams initially appeared as a recurring cast member,<ref name=\"THR082809\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/blogs/live-feed/jesse-williams-cast-greys-anatomy-52136|title=Jesse Williams cast in 'Grey's Anatomy'|date=August 28, 2009|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=December 7, 2013}}</ref> and was later promoted to a series regular in [[Grey's Anatomy (season 7)|season seven]].<ref name=\"EW060810\">{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2010/06/08/greys-anatomy-jesse-williams-series-regular/|title='Grey's Anatomy' exclusive: Jesse Williams gets full-time upgrade|date=June 8, 2010|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|authorlink=Michael Ausiello|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> The character's  main storyline involves Jackson trying to achieve success on his own instead of riding on the coattails of his surgeon grandfather's high reputation.\n\n==Storylines==\nJackson Avery (played by Jesse Williams) is the grandson of Harper Avery, one of the most famous [[surgery|surgeons]] in the country and the namesake of the prestigious Harper Avery Award. The younger Avery grew up hearing at his grandfather's dinner table about the nobility of being a surgeon, which inspired him to pursue that career. His father \"ran off to God knows where because he couldn't stand the pressure of being an Avery\", and his mother Catherine raised him alone. He says that in his family, he was identified as \"just the pretty one\" and they never pushed him academically, so he pushed himself. Jackson is initially a [[Residency (medicine)|surgical resident]] at Mercy West Hospital. Alongside [[April Kepner]] ([[Sarah Drew]]), Reed Adamson ([[Nora Zehetner]]), and Charles Percy ([[Robert Baker (actor)|Robert Baker]]), he joins the staff at Seattle Grace Mercy West after the institutions are merged. His grandfather Harper Avery is affiliated with Harvard and has to be treated at the hospital; during this period, he tries to convince his grandson to transfer to [[Massachusetts General Hospital]], which he can arrange, but the younger Avery refuses.\n\nIn the aftermath of a mass shooting at SGMW, in which 11 people are killed, Avery suffers [[PTSD]]. For comfort, he and Kepner both take rooms in the large house of fellow resident [[Meredith Grey]] ([[Ellen Pompeo]]). Also living there are her husband, [[Derek Shepherd]] ([[Patrick Dempsey]]), resident [[Alex Karev]] and intern [[Lexie Grey]] ([[Chyler Leigh]]), her half-sister. For some time, Avery suffers because of the death of his friend Percy in the shooting, and having assisted in surgery on Shepherd while threatened at gunpoint by the shooter. The [[Grey's Anatomy (season 7)|seventh season]] shows Avery's emerging interest in Meredith's sister, Lexie Grey, and they start a relationship. Avery also starts working with chief of [[plastic surgery]] [[Mark Sloan (Grey's Anatomy)|Mark Sloan]] ([[Eric Dane]]), who had previously had a relationship with Lexie. She is discomfited by the two men working together and, when she later shows that she still has feelings for Sloan, Avery breaks up with her.\n\nAs the end of the fifth year of residency is near, the surgical residents, including Avery, prepare for their [[board certification]]s as they prepare for fellowships. The night before taking the exam, Jackson and April Kepner have sexual intercourse. However, Kepner is a virgin and regrets having broken her promise to [[Jesus]] to stay a virgin until marriage, the two have sex again during the period of the exams. During the exam, Avery is supported by his mother Catherine ([[Debbie Allen]]), who happens to be a tester at the exams.\n\nAvery, Meredith Grey, [[Cristina Yang]], and [[Alex Karev]] eventually pass their boards, while Kepner fails. Although Avery has true feelings for her, she pushes him away because she believes that he feels guilty for having sex with her. In the [[Flight (Grey's Anatomy)|season eight finale]], Avery reveals to April that he is taking the position at [[Tulane Medical Center]], despite feeling sick for leaving Seattle Grace Mercy West and her behind. As a celebration of the conclusion of their residencies, the former chief of surgery [[Richard Webber]] ([[James Pickens, Jr.]]) organizes his annual dinner for them. The [[Grey's Anatomy (season 8)|eighth season]] ends with Avery, Karev, Kepner, and Webber waiting for Meredith and Yang. They are victims of an [[aviation accident]] in which Lexie Grey and eventually Mark Sloan die of their injuries.\n\nAfter the accident, Avery stays at Seattle Grace and continues his work in plastic surgery. He and Kepner continue a sexual relationship, although April is uneasy and believes she is pregnant. When she tells Avery, he proposes to her and she accepts, anticipating a happy wedding. But the pregnancy is false and the couple break up before announcing their engagement to the staff. As a means to avoid each other, the two doctors decide to each bring a date to [[Miranda Bailey|Dr. Bailey]]'s wedding, both of whom are interns.\n\nAfter the wedding, Avery has sex in his car with his date, intern Stephanie Edwards ([[Jerrika Hinton]]). Shortly afterwards he tells Kepner about the incident, and she thanks him for his honesty. It is hinted that Avery still loves Kepner when she turns to him for dating advice and he shows jealousy. They re-establish a friendship. When the hospital faces a financial crisis, Avery's mother Catherine agrees to invest in the hospital via the Harper Avery foundation; but she insists that Avery be made chairman. The board (at Avery's suggestion) later renames the hospital as Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital. Kepner gets engaged to Matthew but at their wedding, Avery stands up to profess his love for her.\n\nKepner chooses Avery, and they run out of her wedding together. When Kepner regrets her decision, Avery proposes to her and they elope. They keep their marriage a secret from the rest of the hospital staff, because of a new rule restricting relations among the staff. Avery's ex-girlfriend Stephanie feels especially betrayed because of how he left her. Catherine Avery is not happy about her son's eloping with Kepner, as he failed to make a prenuptial agreement to protect the Avery family fortune. They make up after Kepner sign such an agreement.\n\nJackson and April soon hit a rough patch when they realize that they have different views about the way their children should be raised with respect to religion. Soon after their fight, April realizes she is pregnant. April and Jackson's baby is diagnosed during pregnancy with Osteogenesis Imperfecta type 2, and they learn that the baby will not survive long after birth. Jackson believes that termination is the best option; however, April would rather give birth to the baby, knowing it will not live very long. They schedule an induction for the next day, and at the beginning of the appointment they are asked to sign their baby's death certificate, which is too hard for the couple to bear. April doesn't sign the papers and returns to work the same day praying for a miracle, while at work she has a heart to heart with a lady who lost her fianc\u00e9e the night before. They decide to give birth to the baby via induction at 24 weeks gestation, having it baptized right then. She gives birth to Samuel Norbert Avery and he passes away shortly after birth.\n\nIn the series 11 finale, Kepner tells Avery that she is leaving with [[Owen Hunt]] to serve as a trauma surgeon in the Army; it will help her grieve for their son. Avery lets her go and wonders how he can deal with his own grief.  After discussions over the phone via Facetime, Kepner tells Avery that she is extending her service time. The sound of gunfire and explosions are heard at April's base camp, leaving her to quickly terminate the call. On Valentine's Day, Kepner returns to the hospital, where she and Avery embrace in the foyer.\n\nIn season 12, their marriage begins to fall apart and they grow estranged.  In episode 11, they file for a civil divorce.  After their divorce is completed, Kepner reveals that she is pregnant with Avery's child. In season 14, Jackson begins a relationship with [[Maggie Pierce]].\n\n==Development==\n\n===Casting and creation===\nIn February 2009, [[Michael Ausiello]] hinted at the possibility of central character, [[Meredith Grey]] ([[Ellen Pompeo]]), having another sibling.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2009/02/25/greys-exclusive-3/|title='Grey's' exclusive: Does Mer have another MIA sibling?|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|authorlink=Michael Ausiello|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|date=February 25, 2009|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> The series had released a casting call for an actor who could pass as biracial; casting was postponed until season six.<ref name=\"Fancast120809\">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091212085721/http://www.fancast.com/blogs/greys-anatomy/is-mer-getting-a-brother-greys-star-speaks-out/|url=http://www.fancast.com/blogs/greys-anatomy/is-mer-getting-a-brother-greys-star-speaks-out/|title=Grey's Anatomy's Jesse Williams Addresses Meredith's Brother Rumor|date=December 8, 2009|first=Matt|last=Webb Mitovich|archivedate=December 12, 2009|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> Williams's casting was announced in late August 2009. Though his name is not given, the character's arc was expected to last several episodes.<ref name=\"THR082809\"/> Williams described his audition as a \"simple process.\" He got the information on his birthday, August 5, and went in the next day to read for the role, despite not knowing what part he had auditioned for. Williams learned he got the job a week later.<ref name=\"Essence102209\">{{cite web|url=http://www.essence.com/2009/10/21/jesse-williams-heats-up-greys-anatomy/|title=Jesse Williams Heats Up 'Grey's Anatomy'|date=October 22, 2009|work=[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> In late 2009, a casting call for a young [[Ellis Grey]] ([[Kate Burton (actress)|Kate Burton]]) and a young [[Richard Webber]] ([[James Pickens, Jr.]]), who would appear in flashbacks, fueled rumors that Avery could be Meredith's half-brother. Williams later shot down the rumor, saying that Meredith would have noticed if her mother were pregnant. Matt Webb Mitovich noted Williams's absence from the \"''Seattle Grace: On Call''\" [[webseries]] as a sign of big plans for the character.<ref name=\"Fancast120809\"/>\n\nIn the episode, \"[[Perfect Little Accident]],\" which premiered on March 4, 2010, Avery is revealed to be the grandson of the legendary [[Harper Avery]] ([[Chelcie Ross]]).<ref>{{Cite episode |title= Perfect Little Accident |episodelink= Perfect Little Accident |url= |credits= Peter Nowalk (writer); Bill D'Elia (director)|accessdate= December 8, 2013 |series= Grey's Anatomy |serieslink= Grey's Anatomy |first= |last= |network= [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |station= |city= |date= March 4, 2010 |began= |ended= |season= 6 |seriesno= |number= 16 |minutes= |time= |transcript= |transcripturl= |quote= |language=English}}</ref> Shonda Rhimes hinted at the possibility of Williams and his co-star [[Sarah Drew]] becoming series regulars in her blog post about the season finale in May 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2010/05/21/greys-anatomy-season-finale-scoop/|title=Exclusive: 'Grey's Anatomy' boss answers your burning season finale questions|date=May 21, 2010|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|authorlink=Michael Ausiello|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> Williams's promotion was eventually confirmed in June 2010.<ref name=\"EW060810\"/>\n\n===Characterization===\nThe character's profile on official ''ABC'' website describes Avery as \"hardworking, driven, observant\" and \"eager.\" However, at times, Avery can be too confident and \"overly competitive,\" and very \"stubborn.\" He has a habit of teasing his coworkers.<ref name=\"ABC.com\"/> Williams revealed to [[Essence (magazine)|Essence.com]] that his character is very \"ambitious. He doesn't takes sides or deal with any drama. He's there to work and not really get involved in the pettiness.\" He describes the character as much more \"cavalier,\" and bold.<ref name=\"Essence102209\"/> Matt Webb Mitovitch described Jackson as having a \"sense of entitlement,\" while Williams described Jackson's demeanor as \"swagger.\" Because his work environment is extremely competitive, Avery acts as if he belongs and refuses to second guess himself.<ref name=\"Fancast120809\"/> Upon arrival at Seattle Grace, he is \"kind of a wise ass surgeon.\" He feels he is an \"invader\" in the new team and \"he decides to deal with it kind of aggressively and not shy away from it and show his personality. He is very confident and likes to say what is on his mind.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Jesse Williams Talks Joining The 'Grey's Anatomy' Cast|url=http://watch.accesshollywood.com/video/jesse-williams-talks-joining-the-greys-anatomy-cast/1311787025001?&page=18|work=[[Access Hollywood]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal Television Distribution]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211190425/http://watch.accesshollywood.com/video/jesse-williams-talks-joining-the-greys-anatomy-cast/1311787025001?&page=18|archivedate=December 11, 2013}}</ref> Williams also said: \"Jackson is more of a lone wolf. He's not really built to go seek support and a shoulder to cry on.\"<ref>{{cite web|title='Grey's Anatomy's' Jesse Williams on Jackson's Personal, Professional Battles|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/greys-anatomy-spoilers-jesse-williams-jackson-april-stephanie-428484|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|first=Lesley|last=Goldberg|accessdate=December 8, 2013|date=March 13, 2013}}</ref> \"He's always been trying to make it on his own. Jackson doesn't want to live off his legacy and his name, which also conflicts with him wanting to be close to his mother.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Abrams|first=Natalie|title=Grey's Anatomy's Jesse Williams on Catherine Avery's Arrival and \"Jaxie's\" Future|url=http://www.tvguide.com/news/greys-anatomy-jesse-williams-1038670.aspx|work=[[TV Guide]]|publisher=[[Lions Gate Entertainment]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013|date=October 12, 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Relationships===\nJackson immediately clashes with [[Cristina Yang]] ([[Sandra Oh]]) due to their competitive natures. The immediate tension between the duo leads to speculation about a potential romance.<ref name=\"Betty102609.2\">{{cite web|url=http://bettyconfidential.com/ar/ld/a/The-Betty-Interview-Jesse-Williams.html?page=2|page=2|title=The Betty Interview: Jesse Williams|date=October 26, 2009|first=Patty|last=Adams|work=[[BettyConfidential]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213122102/http://bettyconfidential.com/ar/ld/a/The-Betty-Interview-Jesse-Williams.html?page=2|archivedate=December 13, 2013}}</ref> Yang and Avery compete for the same cases, and in the episode, \"[[Invest in Love]],\" for the first time, Jackson witnesses Cristina taking charge of a situation, and he admires her; he looks at her differently. At a party, when Jackson is a bit drunk, he opens up about how attractive he finds Cristina and kisses her. Jackson is unaware of Yang's relationship with [[Owen Hunt]] ([[Kevin McKidd]]), so the attraction is natural. Williams does not worry about fans of the couple hating his character because he understands that fans aren't really supposed to like the Mercy Westers; Jackson is in the enemy camp and \"has to take his lumps.\" Williams said the kiss was a \"pretty relatable crime of passion.\" The kiss doesn't have any immediate effects on Owen and Cristina's romance and it remains secret.<ref name=\"TVG110509\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/GreyAnatomy-Jackson-Cristina-1011684.aspx|title=Grey's Anatomy: Jesse Williams Dissects the Jackson-Cristina Kiss|date=November 5, 2009|first=Natalie|last=Abrams|work=[[TV Guide]]|publisher=[[Lions Gate Entertainment]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> Jackson and Cristina develop a sort of mutual understanding as they tend to push one another to be better.\n\nSpeaking of Jackson's past relationship with [[Lexie Grey]], Williams said: \"He tried to be safe and wise and not deal with girls, really, when he first focused on transitioning into Seattle Grace from Mercy West. He kept his head down, got his work done and didn\u2019t get caught up with banging nurses or anything. But he couldn\u2019t help himself with Lexie once they got close; he really kind of fell for her. He made himself vulnerable probably to the least available person in the hospital, because he knew that she had a longstanding relationship with Mark. He knew he shouldn\u2019t head in that direction, but he went against his better judgment and got burned for it.\"<ref name=\"s8finale\">{{cite web|title=Grey's Anatomy Preview: Jesse Williams Talks Jackson, April, Lexie and the 'Bittersweet' Finale|url=http://tvline.com/2012/05/03/greys-anatomy-season-8-episode-22-jesse-williams/|work=[[TVLine]]|publisher=[[PMC (company)|PMC]]|first=Matt|last=Webb Mitovich|accessdate=December 8, 2013|date=May 3, 2012}}</ref> \"They are both kind of suckers for love [...] they both get caught up in their own momentum [...] he's all about his job and pressure from his grandfather but then he gets bowled over with this platonic relationship. Avery just can't help himself with Lexie.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Jesse Williams: I'm Excited For Jackson To Grow His Relationship With Lexie On 'Grey's Anatomy'!|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2011/05/23/jesse-williams-greys-anatomy-season-eight-spoilers-lexie-jackson-mark-meredith-derek/|work=Hollywood Life|first1=Lorena|last1=O'Neil|first2=Kristin|last2=Benson|accessdate=December 8, 2013|date=May 23, 2011}}</ref>he is  very hot \n\nAt the end of the eighth season, April and Jackson's friendship evolved into an intimate relationship: \"I thought they were going to be able to walk the line of staying on the friendship side of things. What they have is kind of really unique and organic in the world of ''Grey\u2019s Anatomy'' \u2013 two genders in a completely platonic, wholesome, pleasant and productive relationship/friendship. Who is to say that has to end?\"<ref name=\"s8finale\"/> In the ninth season, Jackson started a relationship with intern Stephanie Edward. Williams gave his insight: \"That's a relationship that is fun, light, and no strings attached. She's sweet. She's funny. They aren't bogged down by these big notions of each other.<ref>{{cite web|last=McKenna|first=Sean|title=Grey's Anatomy Q&A: Jesse Williams on Becoming the New Boss|url=http://www.tvfanatic.com/2013/03/greys-anatomy-qanda-jesse-williams-on-becoming-the-new-boss/|work=TV Fanatic|publisher=[[SheKnows Media|SheKnows Entertainment]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013|date=March 14, 2013}}</ref>\nJackson later declares his love for April at her wedding to EMT Matthew. They get married and have a child together, but he dies shortly after birth. Distraught and searching for purpose, April turns to the army and goes on tour with Owen, leaving Jackson at Grey-Sloan Memorial. After extending her leave several times, Jackson gives April an ultimatum that if she does not return immediately to Seattle, their relationship is over. April does not immediately return, and when she finally does, Jackson feels that April does not respect his needs in the relationship, especially after losing a child. The two try to make it work, but eventually come to the decision to end their marriage. April discover she's pregnant the day of their divorce proceedings, but does not disclose this until after the papers have been signed. In the fourteenth season Jackson begins a relationship with [[Maggie Pierce]].\n\n== Reception ==\n{{Expand section|date=June 2013}}\nMargaret Lyons of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' wrote the addition of Avery's character to the show was one of the 10 reasons she loves ''Grey's Anatomy'' again: \"Dr. Avery wasn't quite clicking as part of the ensemble when Jesse Williams first joined the cast. But now? Oh, mama. He's flirty \u2014 to a fault \u2014 but he's also a decent dude, and the show was in need of a seriously single male character.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lyons|first=Margaret|title='Grey's Anatomy': 10 Reasons We Love It Again!|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/gallery/0,,20302134_20439143_20871343,00.html#20870915|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.|Time Inc]]|accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=November 4, 2010}}</ref> His [[bromance]] with mentor Mark Sloan has been positively received.<ref>{{cite web|last=Morrison|first=Courtney|title=Grey's Anatomy Midseason Report Card: B+|url=http://www.tvfanatic.com/2011/11/greys-anatomy-midseason-report-card-b/|work=TV Fanatic|publisher=[[SheKnows Media|SheKnows Entertainment]]|accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=November 18, 2011}}</ref> Janalen Samson of [[BuddyTV]] commented: \"these scenes with Jesse Williams are proving to be gems. I do love a good Bromance and these two actors are bringing the love and the funny in spades.<ref>{{cite web|last=Samson |first=Janalen |title='Grey's Anatomy' Fan Columnist: Love Is All You Need |url=http://www.buddytv.com/articles/greys-anatomy/greys-anatomy-fan-columnist-lo-43907.aspx|work=BuddyTV|accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=February 9, 2012}}</ref> The pairing was included in [[Zap2it]]'s 25 Top Bromances of 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Zap2it's 25 Top Bromances of 2012|url=http://www.zap2it.com/news/pictures/zap-zap2its-25-top-bromances-of-2012-pics,0,89883.photogallery?index=23|work=[[Zap2it]]|accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=December 19, 2012}}</ref> Reviewing the first part of the [[Grey's Anatomy (season 9)|ninth season]], Lyons said: \"Avery's mom is more interesting than he is.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lyons|first=Margaret|title=Now That Private Practice Is Over, Addison Should Go Back to Grey's Anatomy|url=http://www.vulture.com/2013/01/greys-anatomy-needs-addison-private-practice.html|work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|accessdate=February 1, 2013|date=January 23, 2013}}</ref> He was listed in [[Wetpaint]]'s \"10 Hottest Male Doctors on TV\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Martin|first=Rebecca|title=The 10 Hottest Male Doctors on TV|url=http://www.wetpaint.com/greys-anatomy/gallery/the-10-hottest-male-doctors-on-tv#7|work=[[Wetpaint]]|publisher=The Cambio Network|accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=December 21, 2012}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130515135632/http://abc.go.com/shows/greys-anatomy/bio/jackson-avery/568571 Jackson Avery] at [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC.com]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20170419010547/http://www.imdb.com/character/ch0169549/ Jackson Avery] on [[IMDb]]\n\n{{Grey's Anatomy}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Avery, Jackson}}\n[[Category:Fictional characters from California]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 2009]]\n[[Category:Fictional surgeons]]\n[[Category:Grey's Anatomy characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional African-American people]]\n[[Category:Male characters in television]]\n", "text_old": "{{Lead too short|date=May 2012}}\n{{Infobox character\n| name = Jackson Avery\n| series = [[Grey's Anatomy]]\n| image = [[File:Jesse-williams-greys.jpg|220px]]\n| caption = The [[Grey's Anatomy (season 9)|Season 9]] Promotional Photo of [[Jesse Williams (actor)|Jesse Williams]] as '''Dr. Jackson Avery'''\n| portrayer = [[Jesse Williams (actor)|Jesse Williams]]\n| first = \"[[Invasion (Grey's Anatomy)|Invasion]]\" (6.05) <br> October 15, 2009 <br> (as recurring cast) <br> \"[[Grey's Anatomy (season 7)#ep127|With You I'm Born Again]]\" (7.01) <br> September 23, 2010 <br> (as series regular)\n| creator = [[Shonda Rhimes]]\n| occupation = [[Attending physician|Attending]] [[Plastic surgery|plastic surgeon]] and [[Otolaryngology|ENT]]<br>Board [[Chairman]] of Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital\n| title = Chief of Plastic Surgery<br>[[Doctor of Medicine|M.D]]<br>[[Fellow of the American College of Surgeons|F.A.C.S.]]\n| spouse = {{marriage|[[April Kepner]]|2013|2016|reason=divorced}}\n| children = Samuel Norbert Avery (son via April, deceased) <br>Harriet Kepner-Avery (daughter via April) \n| significant_other = [[Lexie Grey]] <br> [[Stephanie Edwards (Grey's Anatomy)|Stephanie Edwards]] <br> [[Maggie Pierce]] <br> Victoria \"Vic\" Hughes <br> \u2018Priya\u2019\n| family = Robert Avery (father)<br>Catherine Avery (mother)<br>Harper Avery (paternal grandfather, deceased)<br> [[Richard Webber]] (step-father)\n}}\n'''Jackson Avery''', [[Doctor of Medicine|M.D.]] is a fictional character in the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] [[prime time]] [[medical drama]], ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'', portrayed by actor [[Jesse Williams (actor)|Jesse Williams]].<ref name=\"ABC.com\">{{cite web|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/greys-anatomy/bios/jackson-avery|title=Jesse Williams as Jackson Avery|work=[[Grey's Anatomy]]|publisher=[[American Broadcasting Company]]|accessdate=December 7, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104031102/http://abc.go.com/shows/greys-anatomy/bios/jackson-avery|archivedate=November 4, 2013}}</ref> The character was created by series creator and executive producer, [[Shonda Rhimes]]. He was introduced in [[Grey's Anatomy (season 6)|season six]] episode \"[[Invasion (Grey's Anatomy)|Invasion]]\" as a surgical resident formerly from Mercy West Medical Center when it merges with Seattle Grace Hospital.\n\nWilliams initially appeared as a recurring cast member,<ref name=\"THR082809\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/blogs/live-feed/jesse-williams-cast-greys-anatomy-52136|title=Jesse Williams cast in 'Grey's Anatomy'|date=August 28, 2009|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=December 7, 2013}}</ref> and was later promoted to a series regular in [[Grey's Anatomy (season 7)|season seven]].<ref name=\"EW060810\">{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2010/06/08/greys-anatomy-jesse-williams-series-regular/|title='Grey's Anatomy' exclusive: Jesse Williams gets full-time upgrade|date=June 8, 2010|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|authorlink=Michael Ausiello|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> The character's  main storyline involves Jackson trying to achieve success on his own instead of riding on the coattails of his surgeon grandfather's high reputation.\n\n==Storylines==\nJackson Avery (played by Jesse Williams) is the grandson of Harper Avery, one of the most famous [[surgery|surgeons]] in the country and the namesake of the prestigious Harper Avery Award. The younger Avery grew up hearing at his grandfather's dinner table about the nobility of being a surgeon, which inspired him to pursue that career. His father \"ran off to God knows where because he couldn't stand the pressure of being an Avery\", and his mother Catherine raised him alone. He says that in his family, he was identified as \"just the pretty one\" and they never pushed him academically, so he pushed himself. Jackson is initially a [[Residency (medicine)|surgical resident]] at Mercy West Hospital. Alongside [[April Kepner]] ([[Sarah Drew]]), Reed Adamson ([[Nora Zehetner]]), and Charles Percy ([[Robert Baker (actor)|Robert Baker]]), he joins the staff at Seattle Grace Mercy West after the institutions are merged. His grandfather Harper Avery is affiliated with Harvard and has to be treated at the hospital; during this period, he tries to convince his grandson to transfer to [[Massachusetts General Hospital]], which he can arrange, but the younger Avery refuses.\n\nIn the aftermath of a mass shooting at SGMW, in which 11 people are killed, Avery suffers [[PTSD]]. For comfort, he and Kepner both take rooms in the large house of fellow resident [[Meredith Grey]] ([[Ellen Pompeo]]). Also living there are her husband, [[Derek Shepherd]] ([[Patrick Dempsey]]), resident [[Alex Karev]] and intern [[Lexie Grey]] ([[Chyler Leigh]]), her half-sister. For some time, Avery suffers because of the death of his friend Percy in the shooting, and having assisted in surgery on Shepherd while threatened at gunpoint by the shooter. The [[Grey's Anatomy (season 7)|seventh season]] shows Avery's emerging interest in Meredith's sister, Lexie Grey, and they start a relationship. Avery also starts working with chief of [[plastic surgery]] [[Mark Sloan (Grey's Anatomy)|Mark Sloan]] ([[Eric Dane]]), who had previously had a relationship with Lexie. She is discomfited by the two men working together and, when she later shows that she still has feelings for Sloan, Avery breaks up with her.\n\nAs the end of the fifth year of residency is near, the surgical residents, including Avery, prepare for their [[board certification]]s as they prepare for fellowships. The night before taking the exam, Jackson and April Kepner have sexual intercourse. However, Kepner is a virgin and regrets having broken her promise to [[Jesus]] to stay a virgin until marriage, the two have sex again during the period of the exams. During the exam, Avery is supported by his mother Catherine ([[Debbie Allen]]), who happens to be a tester at the exams.\n\nAvery, Meredith Grey, [[Cristina Yang]], and [[Alex Karev]] eventually pass their boards, while Kepner fails. Although Avery has true feelings for her, she pushes him away because she believes that he feels guilty for having sex with her. In the [[Flight (Grey's Anatomy)|season eight finale]], Avery reveals to April that he is taking the position at [[Tulane Medical Center]], despite feeling sick for leaving Seattle Grace Mercy West and her behind. As a celebration of the conclusion of their residencies, the former chief of surgery [[Richard Webber]] ([[James Pickens, Jr.]]) organizes his annual dinner for them. The [[Grey's Anatomy (season 8)|eighth season]] ends with Avery, Karev, Kepner, and Webber waiting for Meredith and Yang. They are victims of an [[aviation accident]] in which Lexie Grey and eventually Mark Sloan die of their injuries.\n\nAfter the accident, Avery stays at Seattle Grace and continues his work in plastic surgery. He and Kepner continue a sexual relationship, although April is uneasy and believes she is pregnant. When she tells Avery, he proposes to her and she accepts, anticipating a happy wedding. But the pregnancy is false and the couple break up before announcing their engagement to the staff. As a means to avoid each other, the two doctors decide to each bring a date to [[Miranda Bailey|Dr. Bailey]]'s wedding, both of whom are interns.\n\nAfter the wedding, Avery has sex in his car with his date, intern Stephanie Edwards ([[Jerrika Hinton]]). Shortly afterwards he tells Kepner about the incident, and she thanks him for his honesty. It is hinted that Avery still loves Kepner when she turns to him for dating advice and he shows jealousy. They re-establish a friendship. When the hospital faces a financial crisis, Avery's mother Catherine agrees to invest in the hospital via the Harper Avery foundation; but she insists that Avery be made chairman. The board (at Avery's suggestion) later renames the hospital as Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital. Kepner gets engaged to Matthew but at their wedding, Avery stands up to profess his love for her.\n\nKepner chooses Avery, and they run out of her wedding together. When Kepner regrets her decision, Avery proposes to her and they elope. They keep their marriage a secret from the rest of the hospital staff, because of a new rule restricting relations among the staff. Avery's ex-girlfriend Stephanie feels especially betrayed because of how he left her. Catherine Avery is not happy about her son's eloping with Kepner, as he failed to make a prenuptial agreement to protect the Avery family fortune. They make up after Kepner sign such an agreement.\n\nJackson and April soon hit a rough patch when they realize that they have different views about the way their children should be raised with respect to religion. Soon after their fight, April realizes she is pregnant. April and Jackson's baby is diagnosed during pregnancy with Osteogenesis Imperfecta type 2, and they learn that the baby will not survive long after birth. Jackson believes that termination is the best option; however, April would rather give birth to the baby, knowing it will not live very long. They schedule an induction for the next day, and at the beginning of the appointment they are asked to sign their baby's death certificate, which is too hard for the couple to bear. April doesn't sign the papers and returns to work the same day praying for a miracle, while at work she has a heart to heart with a lady who lost her fianc\u00e9e the night before. They decide to give birth to the baby via induction at 24 weeks gestation, having it baptized right then. She gives birth to Samuel Norbert Avery and he passes away shortly after birth.\n\nIn the series 11 finale, Kepner tells Avery that she is leaving with [[Owen Hunt]] to serve as a trauma surgeon in the Army; it will help her grieve for their son. Avery lets her go and wonders how he can deal with his own grief.  After discussions over the phone via Facetime, Kepner tells Avery that she is extending her service time. The sound of gunfire and explosions are heard at April's base camp, leaving her to quickly terminate the call. On Valentine's Day, Kepner returns to the hospital, where she and Avery embrace in the foyer.\n\nIn season 12, their marriage begins to fall apart and they grow estranged.  In episode 11, they file for a civil divorce.  After their divorce is completed, Kepner reveals that she is pregnant with Avery's child. In season 14, Jackson begins a relationship with [[Maggie Pierce]].\n\n==Development==\n\n===Casting and creation===\nIn February 2009, [[Michael Ausiello]] hinted at the possibility of central character, [[Meredith Grey]] ([[Ellen Pompeo]]), having another sibling.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2009/02/25/greys-exclusive-3/|title='Grey's' exclusive: Does Mer have another MIA sibling?|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|authorlink=Michael Ausiello|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|date=February 25, 2009|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> The series had released a casting call for an actor who could pass as biracial; casting was postponed until season six.<ref name=\"Fancast120809\">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091212085721/http://www.fancast.com/blogs/greys-anatomy/is-mer-getting-a-brother-greys-star-speaks-out/|url=http://www.fancast.com/blogs/greys-anatomy/is-mer-getting-a-brother-greys-star-speaks-out/|title=Grey's Anatomy's Jesse Williams Addresses Meredith's Brother Rumor|date=December 8, 2009|first=Matt|last=Webb Mitovich|archivedate=December 12, 2009|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> Williams's casting was announced in late August 2009. Though his name is not given, the character's arc was expected to last several episodes.<ref name=\"THR082809\"/> Williams described his audition as a \"simple process.\" He got the information on his birthday, August 5, and went in the next day to read for the role, despite not knowing what part he had auditioned for. Williams learned he got the job a week later.<ref name=\"Essence102209\">{{cite web|url=http://www.essence.com/2009/10/21/jesse-williams-heats-up-greys-anatomy/|title=Jesse Williams Heats Up 'Grey's Anatomy'|date=October 22, 2009|work=[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> In late 2009, a casting call for a young [[Ellis Grey]] ([[Kate Burton (actress)|Kate Burton]]) and a young [[Richard Webber]] ([[James Pickens, Jr.]]), who would appear in flashbacks, fueled rumors that Avery could be Meredith's half-brother. Williams later shot down the rumor, saying that Meredith would have noticed if her mother were pregnant. Matt Webb Mitovich noted Williams's absence from the \"''Seattle Grace: On Call''\" [[webseries]] as a sign of big plans for the character.<ref name=\"Fancast120809\"/>\n\nIn the episode, \"[[Perfect Little Accident]],\" which premiered on March 4, 2010, Avery is revealed to be the grandson of the legendary [[Harper Avery]] ([[Chelcie Ross]]).<ref>{{Cite episode |title= Perfect Little Accident |episodelink= Perfect Little Accident |url= |credits= Peter Nowalk (writer); Bill D'Elia (director)|accessdate= December 8, 2013 |series= Grey's Anatomy |serieslink= Grey's Anatomy |first= |last= |network= [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |station= |city= |date= March 4, 2010 |began= |ended= |season= 6 |seriesno= |number= 16 |minutes= |time= |transcript= |transcripturl= |quote= |language=English}}</ref> Shonda Rhimes hinted at the possibility of Williams and his co-star [[Sarah Drew]] becoming series regulars in her blog post about the season finale in May 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2010/05/21/greys-anatomy-season-finale-scoop/|title=Exclusive: 'Grey's Anatomy' boss answers your burning season finale questions|date=May 21, 2010|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|authorlink=Michael Ausiello|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> Williams's promotion was eventually confirmed in June 2010.<ref name=\"EW060810\"/>\n\n===Characterization===\nThe character's profile on official ''ABC'' website describes Avery as \"hardworking, driven, observant\" and \"eager.\" However, at times, Avery can be too confident and \"overly competitive,\" and very \"stubborn.\" He has a habit of teasing his coworkers.<ref name=\"ABC.com\"/> Williams revealed to [[Essence (magazine)|Essence.com]] that his character is very \"ambitious. He doesn't takes sides or deal with any drama. He's there to work and not really get involved in the pettiness.\" He describes the character as much more \"cavalier,\" and bold.<ref name=\"Essence102209\"/> Matt Webb Mitovitch described Jackson as having a \"sense of entitlement,\" while Williams described Jackson's demeanor as \"swagger.\" Because his work environment is extremely competitive, Avery acts as if he belongs and refuses to second guess himself.<ref name=\"Fancast120809\"/> Upon arrival at Seattle Grace, he is \"kind of a wise ass surgeon.\" He feels he is an \"invader\" in the new team and \"he decides to deal with it kind of aggressively and not shy away from it and show his personality. He is very confident and likes to say what is on his mind.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Jesse Williams Talks Joining The 'Grey's Anatomy' Cast|url=http://watch.accesshollywood.com/video/jesse-williams-talks-joining-the-greys-anatomy-cast/1311787025001?&page=18|work=[[Access Hollywood]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal Television Distribution]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211190425/http://watch.accesshollywood.com/video/jesse-williams-talks-joining-the-greys-anatomy-cast/1311787025001?&page=18|archivedate=December 11, 2013}}</ref> Williams also said: \"Jackson is more of a lone wolf. He's not really built to go seek support and a shoulder to cry on.\"<ref>{{cite web|title='Grey's Anatomy's' Jesse Williams on Jackson's Personal, Professional Battles|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/greys-anatomy-spoilers-jesse-williams-jackson-april-stephanie-428484|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|first=Lesley|last=Goldberg|accessdate=December 8, 2013|date=March 13, 2013}}</ref> \"He's always been trying to make it on his own. Jackson doesn't want to live off his legacy and his name, which also conflicts with him wanting to be close to his mother.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Abrams|first=Natalie|title=Grey's Anatomy's Jesse Williams on Catherine Avery's Arrival and \"Jaxie's\" Future|url=http://www.tvguide.com/news/greys-anatomy-jesse-williams-1038670.aspx|work=[[TV Guide]]|publisher=[[Lions Gate Entertainment]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013|date=October 12, 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Relationships===\nJackson immediately clashes with [[Cristina Yang]] ([[Sandra Oh]]) due to their competitive natures. The immediate tension between the duo leads to speculation about a potential romance.<ref name=\"Betty102609.2\">{{cite web|url=http://bettyconfidential.com/ar/ld/a/The-Betty-Interview-Jesse-Williams.html?page=2|page=2|title=The Betty Interview: Jesse Williams|date=October 26, 2009|first=Patty|last=Adams|work=[[BettyConfidential]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213122102/http://bettyconfidential.com/ar/ld/a/The-Betty-Interview-Jesse-Williams.html?page=2|archivedate=December 13, 2013}}</ref> Yang and Avery compete for the same cases, and in the episode, \"[[Invest in Love]],\" for the first time, Jackson witnesses Cristina taking charge of a situation, and he admires her; he looks at her differently. At a party, when Jackson is a bit drunk, he opens up about how attractive he finds Cristina and kisses her. Jackson is unaware of Yang's relationship with [[Owen Hunt]] ([[Kevin McKidd]]), so the attraction is natural. Williams does not worry about fans of the couple hating his character because he understands that fans aren't really supposed to like the Mercy Westers; Jackson is in the enemy camp and \"has to take his lumps.\" Williams said the kiss was a \"pretty relatable crime of passion.\" The kiss doesn't have any immediate effects on Owen and Cristina's romance and it remains secret.<ref name=\"TVG110509\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/GreyAnatomy-Jackson-Cristina-1011684.aspx|title=Grey's Anatomy: Jesse Williams Dissects the Jackson-Cristina Kiss|date=November 5, 2009|first=Natalie|last=Abrams|work=[[TV Guide]]|publisher=[[Lions Gate Entertainment]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> Jackson and Cristina develop a sort of mutual understanding as they tend to push one another to be better.\n\nSpeaking of Jackson's past relationship with [[Lexie Grey]], Williams said: \"He tried to be safe and wise and not deal with girls, really, when he first focused on transitioning into Seattle Grace from Mercy West. He kept his head down, got his work done and didn\u2019t get caught up with banging nurses or anything. But he couldn\u2019t help himself with Lexie once they got close; he really kind of fell for her. He made himself vulnerable probably to the least available person in the hospital, because he knew that she had a longstanding relationship with Mark. He knew he shouldn\u2019t head in that direction, but he went against his better judgment and got burned for it.\"<ref name=\"s8finale\">{{cite web|title=Grey's Anatomy Preview: Jesse Williams Talks Jackson, April, Lexie and the 'Bittersweet' Finale|url=http://tvline.com/2012/05/03/greys-anatomy-season-8-episode-22-jesse-williams/|work=[[TVLine]]|publisher=[[PMC (company)|PMC]]|first=Matt|last=Webb Mitovich|accessdate=December 8, 2013|date=May 3, 2012}}</ref> \"They are both kind of suckers for love [...] they both get caught up in their own momentum [...] he's all about his job and pressure from his grandfather but then he gets bowled over with this platonic relationship. Avery just can't help himself with Lexie.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Jesse Williams: I'm Excited For Jackson To Grow His Relationship With Lexie On 'Grey's Anatomy'!|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2011/05/23/jesse-williams-greys-anatomy-season-eight-spoilers-lexie-jackson-mark-meredith-derek/|work=Hollywood Life|first1=Lorena|last1=O'Neil|first2=Kristin|last2=Benson|accessdate=December 8, 2013|date=May 23, 2011}}</ref>\n\nAt the end of the eighth season, April and Jackson's friendship evolved into an intimate relationship: \"I thought they were going to be able to walk the line of staying on the friendship side of things. What they have is kind of really unique and organic in the world of ''Grey\u2019s Anatomy'' \u2013 two genders in a completely platonic, wholesome, pleasant and productive relationship/friendship. Who is to say that has to end?\"<ref name=\"s8finale\"/> In the ninth season, Jackson started a relationship with intern Stephanie Edward. Williams gave his insight: \"That's a relationship that is fun, light, and no strings attached. She's sweet. She's funny. They aren't bogged down by these big notions of each other.<ref>{{cite web|last=McKenna|first=Sean|title=Grey's Anatomy Q&A: Jesse Williams on Becoming the New Boss|url=http://www.tvfanatic.com/2013/03/greys-anatomy-qanda-jesse-williams-on-becoming-the-new-boss/|work=TV Fanatic|publisher=[[SheKnows Media|SheKnows Entertainment]]|accessdate=December 8, 2013|date=March 14, 2013}}</ref>\nJackson later declares his love for April at her wedding to EMT Matthew. They get married and have a child together, but he dies shortly after birth. Distraught and searching for purpose, April turns to the army and goes on tour with Owen, leaving Jackson at Grey-Sloan Memorial. After extending her leave several times, Jackson gives April an ultimatum that if she does not return immediately to Seattle, their relationship is over. April does not immediately return, and when she finally does, Jackson feels that April does not respect his needs in the relationship, especially after losing a child. The two try to make it work, but eventually come to the decision to end their marriage. April discover she's pregnant the day of their divorce proceedings, but does not disclose this until after the papers have been signed. In the fourteenth season Jackson begins a relationship with [[Maggie Pierce]].\n\n== Reception ==\n{{Expand section|date=June 2013}}\nMargaret Lyons of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' wrote the addition of Avery's character to the show was one of the 10 reasons she loves ''Grey's Anatomy'' again: \"Dr. Avery wasn't quite clicking as part of the ensemble when Jesse Williams first joined the cast. But now? Oh, mama. He's flirty \u2014 to a fault \u2014 but he's also a decent dude, and the show was in need of a seriously single male character.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lyons|first=Margaret|title='Grey's Anatomy': 10 Reasons We Love It Again!|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/gallery/0,,20302134_20439143_20871343,00.html#20870915|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.|Time Inc]]|accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=November 4, 2010}}</ref> His [[bromance]] with mentor Mark Sloan has been positively received.<ref>{{cite web|last=Morrison|first=Courtney|title=Grey's Anatomy Midseason Report Card: B+|url=http://www.tvfanatic.com/2011/11/greys-anatomy-midseason-report-card-b/|work=TV Fanatic|publisher=[[SheKnows Media|SheKnows Entertainment]]|accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=November 18, 2011}}</ref> Janalen Samson of [[BuddyTV]] commented: \"these scenes with Jesse Williams are proving to be gems. I do love a good Bromance and these two actors are bringing the love and the funny in spades.<ref>{{cite web|last=Samson |first=Janalen |title='Grey's Anatomy' Fan Columnist: Love Is All You Need |url=http://www.buddytv.com/articles/greys-anatomy/greys-anatomy-fan-columnist-lo-43907.aspx|work=BuddyTV|accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=February 9, 2012}}</ref> The pairing was included in [[Zap2it]]'s 25 Top Bromances of 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Zap2it's 25 Top Bromances of 2012|url=http://www.zap2it.com/news/pictures/zap-zap2its-25-top-bromances-of-2012-pics,0,89883.photogallery?index=23|work=[[Zap2it]]|accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=December 19, 2012}}</ref> Reviewing the first part of the [[Grey's Anatomy (season 9)|ninth season]], Lyons said: \"Avery's mom is more interesting than he is.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lyons|first=Margaret|title=Now That Private Practice Is Over, Addison Should Go Back to Grey's Anatomy|url=http://www.vulture.com/2013/01/greys-anatomy-needs-addison-private-practice.html|work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|accessdate=February 1, 2013|date=January 23, 2013}}</ref> He was listed in [[Wetpaint]]'s \"10 Hottest Male Doctors on TV\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Martin|first=Rebecca|title=The 10 Hottest Male Doctors on TV|url=http://www.wetpaint.com/greys-anatomy/gallery/the-10-hottest-male-doctors-on-tv#7|work=[[Wetpaint]]|publisher=The Cambio Network|accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=December 21, 2012}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130515135632/http://abc.go.com/shows/greys-anatomy/bio/jackson-avery/568571 Jackson Avery] at [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC.com]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20170419010547/http://www.imdb.com/character/ch0169549/ Jackson Avery] on [[IMDb]]\n\n{{Grey's Anatomy}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Avery, Jackson}}\n[[Category:Fictional characters from California]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 2009]]\n[[Category:Fictional surgeons]]\n[[Category:Grey's Anatomy characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional African-American people]]\n[[Category:Male characters in television]]\n", "name_user": "24.49.35.127", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eRelationships)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jackson_Avery"}
